{
  "texts": [
    "303 Dien [322] 2023 Health/ Academia \"AI hallucination\" refers to the highly susceptible nature of ChatGPT to produce erroneous outputs.",
    "304 Abu-Farha et al. [323] 2023 Health \"AI hallucination\" refers to the generation of scientifically false content that might seem convincing to nonexperts.",
    "305 Tippareddy et al. [324] 2023 Health/ Academia \"AI hallucination\" refers to confident responses generated by ChatGPT without being justified by training data.",
    "306 Oviedo-Trespalacios et al. [325] 2023 ChatGPT \"AI hallucination\" refers to the occurrence where ChatGPT can produce answers that appear credible but may be incorrect or nonsensical.",
    "307 Sarraju et al. [326] 2023 Health/ ChatGPT \"AI hallucination\" refers to Inaccurate information may be presented in a confident manner, including nonexistent references to scientific literature."
  ]
}